International Business Machines Corp Broadens Analytics Portfolio With Acquisition Of Varicent Software Incorporated
Friday, 13 Apr 2012 09:00am EDT
International Business Machines Corp announced a definitive agreement to acquire Varicent Software Incorporated, a provider of analytics software for compensation and sales performance management. Varicent is a privately held company, with headquarters in Toronto, Canada. Financial terms were not disclosed. IBM will combine Varicent with its R&D and prior acquisitions including Algorithmics, Clarity Systems, OpenPages, Cognos and SPSS, to expand IBM capabilities in business analytics and optimization across finance, sales, and customer service operations.Â 
